          "expr": "sum(rate({__name__=~\"OrderProcessorIgnoredEvents_total|order_processor_ignored_events_total\"}[$__rate_interval])) or vector(0)",
          "legendFormat": "IgnoredEvents"
        },
        {
          "refId": "B",
          "expr": "sum(rate({__name__=~\"OrderProcessorDuplicateEvents_total|order_processor_duplicate_events_total\"}[$__rate_interval])) or vector(0)",
          "legendFormat": "DuplicateEvents"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 18,
      "type": "text",
      "title": "Trace View",
      "gridPos": { "h": 7, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 32 },
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "## Trace View\n\n- Open `Explore`, choose datasource `Tempo`, and search traces with span attributes already emitted by the app.\n- Recommended trace filters:\n  - `app.correlation_id=\"demo-001\"`\n  - `app.order_id=\"<order-id>\"`\n  - `service.name=\"order-api\"`\n- Use the API response header `x-correlation-id` to follow the whole request across metrics, logs and traces.\n- Use the API response header `x-trace-id` when you need to compare a Lambda invocation in X-Ray with the same request path in Grafana/Tempo.\n- Note: because the edge is `API Gateway HTTP API`, the trace starts in the Lambda span, not at the API Gateway edge."
      }
    }
  ]
}
